  "body": "**Is this a bug report or feature request?**\r\n* Bug Report\r\n\r\n**Deviation from expected behavior:**\r\n\r\nLaunching a cluster with certain memory request but no memory limit throws the following error:\r\n\r\n```\r\n2019-08-02 10:40:48.595001 E | op-cluster: failed to create cluster in namespace rook-ceph. failed to start the mons. refuse to run the pod with 0mb of ram, provide at least 1024mb.\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe source of the error is in this function: https://github.com/rook/rook/blob/master/pkg/operator/ceph/spec/spec.go#L183\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:**\r\n\r\nRook should be able to run in Burstable mode as explained here: https://github.com/rook/rook/blob/master/design/resource-constraints.md\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (minimal and precise):**\r\n\r\nDefault cluster.yaml but with memory request set.\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n* Rook version (use `rook version` inside of a Rook Pod): master",
